  "prompt": "If I delete someone on Snapchat that I have a streak with, and my account is available for everyone to snap/chat me, will that erase the streak?",
  "response": "Yes, deleting someone on Snapchat will erase your streak with them, regardless of whether your account is public or private.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Mutual Connection Required:** Snapchat streaks are based on consistent communication between two users who are mutually added as friends.\n*   **Deletion Removes Friendship:** Deleting someone removes them from your friend list, breaking that mutual connection.\n*   **Streak Termination:** Once the friendship is broken, the streak is automatically terminated on both ends.\n\nSo, even if your account is set to allow anyone to snap you, the streak will still disappear because you've deleted the other person as a friend.",
